<HEADLINE> EU to Provide Egypt with Fund for Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, February 1 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) will
provide Egypt with a large sum of fund this month to help
modernize the country's industry in the coming years, Egyptian
Minister of Industry Suleiman Reda said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Inspecting a new iron and steel complex in Aswan, 700
kilometers south of Cairo, Reda said the EU will grant Egypt 470
million U.S. dollars to help upgrade its industry, Egypt's Middle
East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the 15-nation European organization will provide
Egypt with a loan of 400 million dollars for the industry
renovation process, the minister said.
</P>
<P>
The plan involving 5,000 industrial firms in the coming five
years has been endorsed by the Egyptian cabinet and will soon be
submitted to the People's Assembly (parliament) for approval, Reda
said.
</P>
<P>
The project is also aimed at establishing 20 specialized
technological centers to supply industrial firms with skilled
laborers, he added.
</P>
<P>
Egypt and the EU have been negotiating for a partnership
agreement, under which the EU will help Egypt carry out a 15-year
Industry Modernization Program to enable it to be better prepared
for international competition in industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
