<HEADLINE> Comoran PM in France for Consultation on Home Situation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Comoran Prime Minister Abbas
Djoussouf is on a visit in France for consultation on the
situation in the Indian Ocean archipelago, which is tormented by a
secessionist movement on two of its three major islands.
</P>
<P>
Djoussouf will talk with the French presidential advisor on
foreign affairs Michel Dupuch and foreign ministry officials, in
the wake of the decision made by the Organization of African Unity
(OAU) on holding a peace conference on the Comoros.
</P>
<P>
Nine African states will send envoys to the Comoros in 10 days
to prepare for such a conference.
</P>
<P>
The Comoros is made up with four islands -- Grande Comore,
Moheli, Anjouan and Mayotte, with the last island being under
French administration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
