<HEADLINE> Iran Seizes 147 Tonnes of Drugs in 10 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Iran said on Monday its police
confiscated over 147 tonnes of various drugs in the first 10
months of the current Iranian calendar year ending March 20.
</P>
<P>
Reza Saremi, an official at the anti-drug headquarters, said
the seized drugs included 118 tonnes of opium, 18 tonnes of
morphine and 11 tonnes of hashish, the Islamic Republic News
Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian Majlis (parliament) passed a strict anti-drug law
in January 1989, under which any one caught with 30 grams of
heroin or five kilograms of opium will be sentenced to death.
</P>
<P>
So far there is no official figures on how many drug smugglers
have been executed since the law took effect, but some reports
put the figure at more than 3,000. 
</P>
