<HEADLINE> NPC Committee Discusses Economic Goals (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 2 (Xinhua) -- The National People's Congress
(NPC) Financial and Economic Committee is currently reviewing the
nation's 1999 economic plan and budget.
</P>
<P>
Five government departments reported to the Committee on issues
concerning implementation of the 1998 plan for national economic
and social development and the budget.
</P>
<P>
Members of the committee reaffirmed the government's role in
scoring a rapid economic growth rate during 1998 in spite of the
impact of the Asian economic crisis and severe summer flooding.
</P>
<P>
Members also voiced a number of opinions on "difficult issues
of public concern," including reform of the state-owned sector,
the national debt, deficits and investment in science research and
education.
</P>
<P>
The law requires preliminary examinations of the economic plan
and budget affairs at least one month before the full annual
session of the NPC which is responsible for adopting the formal
annual economic development plan and budget.
</P>
<P>
Wu Shuqing said that state-owned enterprises still face
difficulties and noted that last year's reform efforts had little
effect.
</P>
<P>
"We have two years left to extricate loss-making state-owned
enterprises from difficulties and transform them into profitable
ones," according to Wu.
</P>
<P>
He said China needs to adopt flexible credit measures to
encourage consumption and stimulate economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Government departments estimated the ratios for budgetary
deficits and accumulative national debts to GDP will hit 1.7 and
10 percent respectively in 1999, with both ratios much lower than
the internationally recognized warning levels.
</P>
<P>
However, Yao Zhenhuai noted that the financial situation of the
central government is subject to a certain degree of risk if it is
in fact the sole debtor.
</P>
<P>
"Related factors must be taken into account when drafting the
central budget," said Yao.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990202.0061 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-02-02 </DATE_TIME>
