official Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Ten F-15 fighter jets, six F-16s, two Prowlers planes, four
tanker aircraft, one AWACS plane and four commander planes took
off from the Incirlik base at hours between 10:00 a.m. and 11:15 a.
m. local time (08:00 and 09:15 GMT) to patrol the no-fly zone in
northern Iraq, said the agency. (Turkey-Iraq-US)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian Prime Minister Yevgeny Primakov on Tuesday
reaffirmed Moscow's determination to join the Organization for
Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD).
</P>
<P>
Primakov told visiting OECD Secretary-General Donald Johnston
that the organization's support is very important for Russia at
this very difficult stage, Interfax reported. (Russia-Primakov-
OECD) 
</P>
