China since the two countries forged diplomatic ties in September
1997. Saint Lucia's decision to establish relations with China was
based on its realization of the importance of fully exercising
sovereignty and the fact that the two nations share common views
on many issues. "Our diplomatic relations have sound ideological
grounding," noted Anthony.
