<HEADLINE> Update: Plane Crashed in Angola's Capital, Killing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-eight people were killed
when a plane crashed into the most densely populated residential
area in Luanda, Angola's capital, Tuesday morning, Angola state
radio said.
</P>
<P>
The Antonov-12 light plane crashed into the Cazenga residential
area 10 minutes after the pilot found a mechanical breakdown, soon
after it took off from the Luanda Airport at about 4 a.m. (0300
gmt).
</P>
<P>
Five houses were destroyed by the crash which also caused a
fire, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
Police who have come to the rescue said that more people may
die in the coming hours as many injured are in serious condition.
</P>
<P>
The plane, owned by a private company, was on its way to the
diamond producing town Lucapa, capital of Luanda-Norte Province
in northeast Angola, and eight people aboard the plane were killed
and the other 20 were killed on the ground.
</P>
<P>
Government officials had earlier said that the plane was
carrying 10 people, who all died. 
</P>
