<HEADLINE> Matthaeus to Captain German Soccer Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, February 2 (Xinhua) -- Lothar Matthaeus will captain the
German soccer team in two friendly games in the United States this
week.
</P>
<P>
Coach Erich Ribbeck said the veteran was a perfect interim
solution as team captain Oliver Bierhoff cannot join the tour
because of playing commitments at AC Milan.
</P>
<P>
The German team will play the United States team on February 6
and Colombia on February 9.
</P>
<P>
Matthaeus, who has captained the German squad 68 times in 130
appearances, said he had no plans to retire from the national team.
</P>
<P>
The Bayern libero, 37, said he was not interested in setting
records by playing in a fifth World Cup and said he wanted to keep
playing as long as he was fit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
