<HEADLINE> Int'l Body Condemns Murder of Aid Worker in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, February 2 (Xinhua) -- The Somalia Aid Coordination
Body (SACB) Monday condemned the murder of Dr. M.S. Bohgal, an
Italian aid worker, in Somali's Gedo Region on January 26.
</P>
<P>
In a written statement issued here, SACB Executive Committee
said that while the events leading to this tragic and horrific
incident remain unclear, the SACB wishes to make it clear that any
atrocity against aid personnel is totally unacceptable and will
not be tolerated under any circumstances.
</P>
<P>
Bohgal belongs to Terra Nova, an Italian humanitarian group,
and the statement did not specify where Gedo region is situated in
the Horn of Africa country.
</P>
<P>
The international body consisting of donors, United Nations
Agencies and international non-governmental organizations
demanded in the statement that relevant local authorities "act
responsibly and expeditiously to bring the perpetrators of this
heinous and repugnant crime to justice".
</P>
<P>
As a response to the crime, the SACB has recommended the
immediate suspension of all current and proposed rehabilitation
activities by international agencies in Gedo region.
</P>
<P>
After two weeks, the SACB will review the situation in light of
 additional information clarifying the circumstances of the murder
as well as the action taken by the local authorities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
