<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia Posts 2.97 Percent inflation in January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, February 2 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's inflation rate in
January was 2.97 percent, lower than that of the same period in
previous year which recorded 6.88 percent, the Central Statistics
Agency said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The higher inflation in January 1998 was caused by a very low
exchange rate of Indonesian rupiah against the U.S. dollars which
reached 15,000 rupiah per dollar in that month, Chief of the
agency Sugito Suwito told a press conference here.
</P>
<P>
The exchange rate in January this year was 8,000 to 9,000
rupiah per dollar.
</P>
<P>
The 2.97 percent inflation in January was due to the increase
of consumer price index, he said.
</P>
<P>
Sugito said the inflation rate from April 1998 to January 1999
was 43.89 percent, compared with 15.97 in the same period of the
previous fiscal year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
