<HEADLINE> State to Guarantee Basic Urban Living Standards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 2 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Civil Affairs
plans to accelerate the establishment of a minimum living standard
system for Chinese urban dwellers.
</P>
<P>
The system, an essential part of the comprehensive social
security network, will be carried out at a crucial point in the
reform of state-run enterprises and will have a dramatic impact on
unemployment and social stability, according to a circular issued
by the Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The ministry noted that the system should be established in
most cities no later than the end of June this year, with
postponement of the deadline to the end of this October applicable
only to areas subject to abject poverty.
</P>
<P>
The circular stressed that establishment of the system is a
realistic measure which will be carried in line with the needs of
economic development and establishing a minimum living standard.
It notes that priority should be given to laid-off workers and
retirees.
</P>
<P>
The nationwide social security system should absorb more
educated staffers with a sense of responsibility and more
regulations are needed to ensure that the system functions
satisfactorily, according to the ministry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
