<HEADLINE> Primakov: Russia Determined to Join OECD </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, February 2 (Xinhua) -- Russian Prime Minister Yevgeny
Primakov on Tuesday reaffirmed Moscow's determination to join the
Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD).
</P>
<P>
Primakov told visiting OECD Secretary-General Donald Johnston
that the organization's support is very important for Russia at
this very difficult stage, Interfax reported.
</P>
<P>
Russia applied for OECD membership in 1996. The Paris-
headquartered organization was established on September 30, 1961,
to promote economic and social welfare in member countries and
stimulate and harmonize efforts to aid developing nations.
</P>
<P>
Johnston arrived here Monday on his own initiative to seek ways
the OECD could help Russia over its financial and economic
difficulties. He was briefed on the country's socio-economic
situation, said Tatiana Aristarkhova, Primakov's press secretary.
</P>
<P>
Johnston also met with Russian First Deputy Prime Minister Yuri
Maslyukov on Tuesday. 
</P>
