<HEADLINE> Beijing Moves to Contain Spreading of AIDS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 2 (Xinhua) -- Medical experts in Beijing
announced today that the capital aims to contain the number of
AIDS patients to under 30,000 by the year 2010.
</P>
<P>
In order to achieve this, Beijing is expected to step up the
detection of AIDS and unveil a set of regulations to prevent the
spreading of the disease.
</P>
<P>
The municipality will also use media coverage to increase
public awareness of AIDS prevention, and include information about
the prevention and treatment of AIDS into the public service
system.
</P>
<P>
By last December, a total of 285 people had been found to be
infected with AIDS, including 105 Beijingers and 65 foreigners.
</P>
<P>
The challenge in preventing AIDS is severe for the city
authorities since the number of AIDS patients found climbed to 96
last year, compared with 20 to 40 in previous years.
</P>
<P>
Beijing has allocated nearly nine million yuan for the
prevention of AIDS during the past ten years, and 37 test centers
have been set up so far, making the detection of the disease
easier. 
</P>
</TEXT>
