<HEADLINE> Indonesia to Import 190,000 Tons of KCL Fertilizer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, February 2 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian government plans
to import 190,000 tons of KCL fertilizer and hundreds of thousands
of tons of other fertilizers to help solve a shortage faced by
farmers, Agriculture Minister Soleh Solahuddin said.
</P>
<P>
"Hopefully, the import plan will allay the worry being felt by
farmers," the minister told reporters after meeting with President
B.J. Habibie at Merdeka Palace here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Soleh was summoned to the Merdeka Palace along with Trade and
Industry Minister Rahardi Ramelan, State Minister for Food Affairs
A.M. Saefuddin and Bank Indonesia Governor Syahril Sabirin for a
discussion of efforts to make this year's paddy planting program a
success.
</P>
<P>
Soleh disclosed the government's KCL fertilizer import plan
after noting that farmers had recently complained about
difficulties in obtaining this type of fertilizer.
</P>
<P>
The price of KCL fertilizer has soared to 1,650 rupiah (about
0.2 U.S. dollar) per kilogram from 850 rupiah after the government
scrapped its subsidy to the fertilizer's price.
</P>
<P>
Replying to questions on the estimated rice output for this
year, Soleh said, production would reach between 50 and 53 million
tons of dried hulled rice compared to last year's output of 46.5
to 47 million tons.
</P>
<P>
The minister said he was optimistic that this year's rice
output would increase as a result of a significant rise in the
amount of farming business credits disbursed this year compared to
last year, namely from 286 billion rupiah to 2.455 trillion rupiah
(about 289 million U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
