<HEADLINE> Veteran Brazilian Cesar to Join Panathinaikos </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, February 2 (Xinhua) -- Borussia Dortmund has agreed to
release veteran Brazilian defender Julio Cesar and allow him to
join Greece's Panathinaikos Athens, the Bundesliga club said in
Dortmund on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Cesar, 35, will move to Greece in a transfer deal worth 300,000
marks (about 173,360 U.S. dollars), Dortmund said.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian angered Dortmund's front office last week when he
left the team's training camp in Turkey, reportedly with a knee
injury. But he failed to consult a Dortmund doctor and instead
reportedly attended to private business in Hamburg.
</P>
<P>
Cesar rejoined Dortmund in November, after a six-month stint
with Botafogo of Rio de Janeiro.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian had already played for Borussia Dortmund between
1994 and 1998, winning the European Champions Cup title in 1987
and the German Bundesliga championships in 1995 and 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
