<HEADLINE> Bank to be Established in Every VDC of Nepal: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, February 2 (Xinhua) -- Nepali Finance Minister
Bharat Mohan Adhikari said Tuesday that a bank or similar
financial institution will be set up in every village development
committee (VDC) of the country in the next five years.
</P>
<P>
He was quoted by the official RSS news agency as saying that
800 banks or financial institutions will be established at 800
VDCs in next 1999/2000 fiscal year, which will collect the
internally inactive capital or savings of the villagers and money
going out of the country from the border areas.
</P>
<P>
He said that he had given directives in this regard to the
Nepal Rastra Bank, the country's central bank.
</P>
<P>
Nepal has a total of 3,995 VDCs in 75 districts. 
</P>
