<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman on Sino-Saint Lucia Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Although there are differences in various respects between the
two countries, such as in population, the size of territories as
well as economic and social systems, the two countries can treat
each other on the basis of equal footing and mutual respect, and
understand and support each other, he added.
</P>
<P>
China always advocated that all countries, big or small, poor
or rich, strong or weak, are equal members of the international
communities, Li said, adding that the development of Sino-Saint
Lucia relations just reflected this principle.
</P>
<P>
Li also described the talks between Anthony and Chinese Premier
Zhu Rongji on Monday as sound.
</P>
<P>
