<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Addresses Global Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
During a meeting with Saint Lucia Prime Minister Kenny Anthony,
Li noted that economic and financial situations have changed
rapidly in Asia and throughout the world over past two years. He
also noted that the financial crisis in Southeast Asia has
provided people across the world with a comprehensive
understanding of economic globalization.
</P>
<P>
Li said that globalization of the world economy provides
opportunities for economic development, and its negative aspects
should not be ignored, especially in terms of the fragile
economies in developing countries.
</P>
<P>
"We should learn to seek benefits and avoid disadvantages in
the process of the economic globalization," said Li.
</P>
<P>
He added that China has consistently considered domestic
conditions while introducing foreign experiences since the
introduction of the reform and opening policies 20 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Anthony voiced agreement with Li, and noted that Saint Lucia
has always worried that economic globalization would damage its
fragile economy.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that economic interests of the developing countries,
especially small countries, should be respected and protected.
</P>
</TEXT>
