<HEADLINE> 109,500 Shares Traded in Tanzanian Stock Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, February 2 (Xinhua) -- The Dar es Salaam Stock
Exchange (DSE) trading session Tuesday recorded a turnover of
109,548 shares worth 65.7 million Tanzanian Shillings (about
95,918 U.S. Dollars) in 11 deals.
</P>
<P>
All the shares sold were from Tanzania Breweries Limited (TBL)
counter, while the Tanzania Oxygen Limited (TOL) counter was
inactive as no shares were traded, according to a statement issued
by the stock exchange, the sole one in the country.
</P>
<P>
A total of 730 TBL shares were sold at 590 Shillings per share
and 108, 818 shares were sold at 600 Shillings per share. The
highest and closing price was 600 Shillings while the lowest and
opening price was 590 Shillings, said the statement, signed by DSE
Chief Executive Officer, H.S. Kibola.
</P>
<P>
At the close of the session, a special-lot order of 3,300,693
TBL shares was on offer at 600 Shillings per share.
</P>
<P>
In addition, 12,032 TBL shares were on offer at 600 Shillings
per share. One thousand TBL shares were on the bid at 580
Shillings per share with no outstanding offer.
</P>
<P>
On TOL counter 230 shares were on offer at 330 Shillings per
share with no outstanding bids, it said.
</P>
<P>
Tanzania Oxygen Limited, a leading manufacturer and distributor
of industrial and medical gases in the country, is the first
public company listed on the stock exchange, launched in last
April.
</P>
<P>
Tanzania Breweries Limited (TBL), a joint venture between the
government and South African Breweries (SAB), came on board in
last August to make the shares market more lively. The government
retains minority shares in the company.
</P>
<P>
The Dar es Salaam Stock Exchange used to open once a week on
Wednesdays. Since mid January this year, its trading sessions are
conducted every Tuesdays and Thursdays between 10:00 and 11:00
a.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
