<HEADLINE> Palestinian Police Arrest Dozens of Hamas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, February 2 (Xinhua) -- Following Monday's killing of
a Palestinian security officer, Palestinian police arrested
dozens of Islamic militant group Hamas members, the Israel Radio
reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The arrests were made overnight in the Palestinian self-rule
areas.
</P>
<P>
A Palestinian security officer was shot dead in the Gaza Strip
on Monday when he tried to arrest three activists of the Hamas
military wing, Izzadin Kassam.
</P>
<P>
The three men also killed a six-year-old Palestinian girl as
they sought to evade capture.
</P>
<P>
They were arrested several hours later in the Shati refugee
camp in the northern Gaza Strip after another gun battle with the
Palestinian police.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, in a related development, Hamas spiritual leader
Sheikh Ahmed Yassin continued the hunger strike on Tuesday,
demanding the release of political prisoners in the jails of the
Palestinian National Authority.
</P>
<P>
Yassin also called on the Palestinian public to join him and to
fast for a day on behalf of the prisoners. 
