<HEADLINE> Shanghai to Open Further </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 2 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai will continue to make
efforts to improve its investment environment and reach a new
level of opening-up this year, Mayor Xu Kuangdi said today.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai will actively engage in technology and service trade
and expand exports by production enterprises, Xu said at a meeting
of the Municipal People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
Efforts will also be made to help qualified private enterprises
to obtain rights to import and export and to develop overseas
processing trade, he said.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that Shanghai's export earnings
reached 16.3 billion US dollars last year, up 10.9 percent from
1997, while its contracted overseas investment totaled 5.8 billion
US dollars. Half of the top industrial multinational corporations
in the world have invested in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Approved by the People's Bank of China, the central bank, 19
overseas banks have been licensed to deal in yuan business in the
Pudong New Area, a rising finance and trade zone separated from
downtown Shanghai by the Huangpu River. 
</P>
