<HEADLINE> Shanghai Plans Nine Percent Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 2 (Xinhua) -- This economic and financial
center of China has set its economic growth rate this year at
around nine percent, according to Mayor Xu Kuangdi today.
</P>
<P>
To that end, Shanghai will try to optimize the economic
structure, increase output and improve efficiency, Xu said in a
work report delivered at a meeting of the Municipal People's
Congress.
</P>
<P>
Efforts must be increased to industrialize new and high
technology, with priority given to the development of the
telecommunications sector, modern biology and the pharmaceutical
industry, and the new materials industry, Xu said.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai will also actively develop the service sector,
attaching greater importance to the information sector and
increasing loans for buying apartments, cars, and other durables,
he said.
</P>
<P>
While the construction of office buildings and shopping malls
will be restricted, that of residential buildings will be
encouraged, Xu said, calling for efforts to further reduce prices
of affordable apartments.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's gross domestic product grew 10.1 percent last year
to more than 360 billion yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
