<HEADLINE> Shanghai Reports Fiscal Surplus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 2 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai reported smooth
implementation of its budgetary arrangements last year, with a
year-end fiscal surplus of 300 million yuan, according to the
Municipal Finance Administration today.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's fiscal revenues totaled 60.87 billion yuan while
expenditure reached 60.5 billion yuan in 1998, administration
chief Liu Hongwei said at a meeting of the Municipal People's
Congress, the local legislature.
</P>
<P>
Liu said that taxes consisted of more than 95 percent of
Shanghai's fiscal revenues last year and spending on urban
infrastructure facilities increased significantly.
</P>
<P>
The major infrastructure projects included the Pudong
International Airport, an elevated ring road, a second subway, and
a central park, she added.
</P>
<P>
Liu revealed that Shanghai has budgeted both its fiscal revenue
and spending this year at 63.58 billion yuan. 
