<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Stresses People's Interests in Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, February 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
has stressed that the committees of the Communist Party of China (
CPC) and governments at all levels must try to uphold and realize
the people's interests in the run up to the 21st century, while
protecting and promoting their initiatives to build a better China.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks during an inspection tour of the Inner
Mongolia Autonomous Region, the first ethnic autonomous region
established in China, from January 28 to February 1.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, also general secretary of the CPC Central Committee,
said the fundamental purpose of the reform and opening-up is to
meet the increasing needs of the people for material and cultural
life, through developing productive forces.
</P>
<P>
"This will also make them work more conscientiously towards the
target and provide a guarantee for the continuous development and
ultimate success of our cause," he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang pointed out that more efforts must be made by the state-
owned enterprises to ensure they give full play to their pivotal
role in the national economy.
</P>
<P>
Party committees and governments at all levels must work hard
to realize the target of the central government to make those
state-owned enterprises in the red get out of difficulty within
three years, he said, and basically introduce a modern enterprise
system among most major state-owned enterprises at the same time.
</P>
<P>
He noted that offering a basic livelihood and reemployment for
laid-off workers is crucial for the reform and development of the
large and medium-sized state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Party committees and governments at all levels must try their
best to help laid-off workers, farmers in poverty-stricken areas
and other people in need, and make sure the relief funds for laid-
off workers and pensions are allocated in time, he said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that this work must be given top priority, as it is
directly related to the smooth progress of the reform and
construction, as well as social stability and progress.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also required the local government and Party committee to
properly handle the issues concerning ethnic groups, noting that
the national unity and common development and prosperity of all
ethnic groups are critical to the future and fate of the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
