<HEADLINE> Plane Crashed in Angola's Capital, Killing 19 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, January 2 (Xinhua) -- At least 19 people were killed
and many others injured when a plane crashed into the most densely
populated residential area in Luanda, Angola's capital, Tuesday
morning.
</P>
<P>
The Antonov-12 light plane crashed into the Cazenga residential
area 10 minutes after the pilot found a mechanical breakdown, soon
after it took off from the Luanda Airport.
</P>
<P>
Five houses were destroyed by the crash which also caused a
fire.
</P>
<P>
Police who have come to the rescue said that more people may
die in the coming hours as many injured are in serious condition.
</P>
<P>
The plane, owned by a private company, was on its way to
Lucapa, capital of Luanda-Norte Province in northeast Angola, with
seven passengers on board beside the crew members.  
</P>
