<HEADLINE> American Trade Fair to Be Held in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, February 2 (Xinhua) -- The American Chamber of
Commerce of Sri Lanka (ACCSL) will hold its fourth American Trade
Fair here from February 8 to 11, according to informed sources
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The trade fair will provide a unique platform for increasing
awareness about American products and services while providing an
opportunity for new American firms to enter the Sri Lankan market,
the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The United States is currently Sri Lanka's biggest trading
partner, accounting for over one-third of all Sri Lankan exports,
and a key source of capital and technological know-how for direct
investment.
</P>
<P>
The sources said more than 60 percent of Sri Lanka's garments
are sent the United States, while other major exports are rubber,
leather products, ceramics, gem and jewelry, toys, sporting
equipment, tea, spices and coffee.
</P>
<P>
About 50 U.S. companies and local businesses with substantial
U.S. investment are now operating in the country and many of them
will participate in the trade fair, the ACCSL sources said.
</P>
<P>
The sources noted that the fair is also intended to help
identity potential distributors in Sri Lanka and encourage new
American firms to enter the Sri Lankan market.
</P>
<P>
The ACCSL, a growing association of 220 Sri Lankan and U.S.
companies, is associated with the U.S. Chamber of Commerce, the
largest business federation in the United States, the sources
said. He added that its main aim is to strengthen and promote
healthy business relations between the two countries for mutual
benefit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
