<HEADLINE> China to Expand Overseas Contracting, Labor Service Sector (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Healthy companies and corporate groups, in particular, will be
encouraged to go abroad and compete for a share of the business on
the international market.
</P>
<P>
The ministry will also step up efforts to explore the potential
for such projects in Africa and Latin America, and to further
cultivate the dwindling markets in east and southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
It will make every effort to encourage business in the Middle
East and tap the market in European Union nations and other
developed countries.
</P>
<P>
The new move is aimed at changing China's dependence on the
Asian market in the project contracting and labor services sectors.
More than 60 percent of China's business within those fields are
currently in Asia.
</P>
