<HEADLINE> Indonesian Parties Stress Environmental Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, February 2 (Xinhua) -- Despite a strong need for U.S.
dollar reserves amid the current economic woes, Indonesia's next
government should adopt an environment-friendly development policy
as its platform, spokesmen of several political parties said.
</P>
<P>
The common views on the significance of putting environmental
protection in the country's development policy were raised by
spokesmen of the ruling Golkar (Functional Group), the United
Development Party (PPP), the Indonesian Democratic Party (PDI),
the National Awakening Party (PKB) and the Moon and Star Party
(PBB) in a dialogue on the environment.
</P>
<P>
In the dialogue, sponsored by Antara News Agency here Tuesday,
the upcoming government has been also urged to continuously
strengthening law enforcement in settling environmental cases.
</P>
<P>
PPP Vice Secretary Bachtiar Chamsyah underscored the weakness
of the legislative body in supervising the government in exploring
natural resources because of the domination of a single majority
political party during 32 years of former President Soeharto's
rule.
</P>
<P>
Under the former government, law enforcement personnel in the
country seemed not to have the courage to bring those who damaged
the environment to court, he said.
</P>
<P>
A similar view was also aired by Marcus Wauran from the PDI,
who said law enforcement in environmental cases should become the
main policy of the next government in a bid to help the country
avoid making the same mistakes as the Soeharto regime.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Abu Hasan Sadzili, a legislator from the ruling
Golkar, said it is high time for the mushrooming political parties
to synchronize the industrial policy to the needs of protecting
the environment.
</P>
<P>
He said the environment is an international issue which the
Indonesian people can not neglect nor separate from political and
economic issues.
</P>
<P>
PBB Vice Secretary Hamzah underlined the urgency of setting up
a special investigation team in the environmental ministry whose
main job is probing each problem dealing with nature and
environmental issues.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia will hold general election on June 7 this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
