<HEADLINE> Investment Forum Opens in Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, February 2 (Xinhua) -- A large investment forum opened
here Tuesday, bringing together 269 companies and organizations
from Lebanon and around the world to seek investment
opportunities in the country.
</P>
<P>
The two-day forum will discuss 26 industrial and agricultural
projects, which were offered by the Lebanese government for foreign
investors.
</P>
<P>
The forum will also address technology transfer, equipment
purchasing, joint-ventures and project finance.
</P>
<P>
Projects on display at the forum, mainly in food and
agro-industrial sectors, will range from a 500,000 U.S. dollars
investment in production of building equipment to a 10 million
dollars investment in a food factory.
</P>
<P>
"One of our main objectives is to attract back investments to
the country's private sector," said Mehdi Hafez, regional
representative of the United Nations Industrial Development
Organization(UNIDO).
</P>
<P>
"In particular, we are encouraging the agro-industrial sector
because we see real potential for exports," he added.
</P>
<P>
The forum is jointly organized by the UNIDO and the Investment
Development Authority of Lebanon which has been encouraging
foreign investment in Lebanese projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
