<HEADLINE> UAE Businessmen Urged to Invest in Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, February 2 (Xinhua) -- A senior official from the
Canadian province of Ontario has called for more investments from
the United Arab Emirates (UAE) in the province, a newspaper report
said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Linking the Canadian and U.S. markets, Ontario has emerged as
the economic powerhouse of Canada, the English daily Khaleej Times
quoted Alberta Al Palladini, Minister for Economic Development,
Trade and Tourism of Ontario, as saying on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a reception hosted by the Canadian Business
Council in Abu Dhabi, Palladini said Ontario is poised to grow
more rapidly than the G-7 economies over the 1998-2000 period.
</P>
<P>
He referred to the sophisticated business services which
anchored a diversified economy in the province where foreign
investments over the last decade stood at about 93 billion
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The visiting Canadian official had talks with his UAE
counterparts from the Abu Dhabi Chamber of Commerce and Industry
(ADCCI).
</P>
<P>
Both sides expressed the will to strengthen economic and trade
cooperation, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Mohammed Omar Abdullah, Director-General of the ADCCI expressed
a keen desire to step up two-way trade between Abu Dhabi and
Ontario.
</P>
<P>
