<HEADLINE> China Urges Macedonia to Revoke Communique with Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 2 (Xinhua) -- China today urged the
Macedonian authorities to correct as soon as possible the serious
mistake of establishing so-called diplomatic relations with Taiwan
and to revoke the relevant communique.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Zhang Qiyue made the
remark in reply to a question at a regular press conference here
this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
She said that the Chinese side has made solemn representations
to the Macedonian government and made clear China's principled
stance on the issue of Taiwan over the past few days.
</P>
<P>
China noticed that the Macedonian president has firmly opposed
the establishment of "diplomatic ties" between Macedonia and
Taiwan and criticized its foreign minister for his decision of
signing the communique with Taiwan, Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
China hopes that the Macedonian authorities will abandon the
illusion of "dual recognition" and bring the Sino-Macedonian
bilateral relationship back to the normal track, she concluded.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
