<HEADLINE> Head of Philippines Charter Reform Body Appointed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, February 2 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph
Estrada has appointed Andres Narvasa, former chief justice of the
Supreme Court, to lead a preparatory body of constitutional
reform, a senior government official said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Executive Secretary Ronaldo Zamora said in a radio interview
that Narvasa will chair the 25-member Preparatory Commission on
Constitutional Reform tasked to recommend amendments to the
country's 1987 constitution.
</P>
<P>
Estrada hopes to complete the roster of members of the
commission in the next two weeks, Zamora said.
</P>
<P>
On November 26 last year, Estrada issued an executive order
creating the Preparatory Commission on Constitutional Reform.
</P>
<P>
Estrada also made it clear that changes in the constitution
will take effect only after his term ends in 2004 and that the
government will keep its hands off the process. 
</P>
