<HEADLINE> Winter Flu Spreads Across U.S. States </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, February 1 (Xinhua) -- U.S. officials said Monday
the winter flu season has abruptly worsened with influenza of flu-
like illnesses reported in almost every state of the country.
</P>
<P>
The number of states with flu outbreaks more than doubled
during the week ending January 23, the latest week for which
figures were available.
</P>
<P>
A week earlier, there were outbreaks in 13 states, the Centers
for Disease Control and Prevention said.
</P>
<P>
The centers said Arizona, Georgia, Massachusetts, Nebraska,
Nevada, North Carolina, Virginia, Washington, and New York City
were hardest hit with flu outbreaks.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show an average of 20,000 people die every year from
complications of flu and pneumonia in the United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
