<DATE_TIME> 1999-02-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Report on China's Stealing U.S. Military </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 2 (Xinhua)-- A U.S. report on China's
stealing U.S. military technology and information through
bilateral economic exchanges is "totally groundless and
irresponsible," said Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokeswoman Zhang
Qiyue at a press conference here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Zhang made the remark when asked to comment on a report that
the Clinton Administration ordered a formal assessment of a U.S.
Congress panel decision that China stole U.S. military technology
through bilateral economic exchanges.
</P>
<P>
She said that Sino-U.S. relations now face new opportunities of
improvement and development and China hopes that the two countries
would make concerted efforts to take a healthy, stable and
constantly growing Sino-U.S. relationship into the next century.
</P>
<P>
China also hopes that U.S. Congress would make positive efforts
to the further development of Sino-U.S. relations, the spokeswoman
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
