<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 5th Dhaka International Trade Fair Begins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, February 2 (Xinhua) -- The Fifth Dhaka International
Trade Fair '99, the largest one of all kinds in the country, began
here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina inaugurated the month-long fair,
which has been organized by the Ministry of Commerce and the
Export Promotion Bureau, aiming to give a boost to the country's
exports.
</P>
<P>
The fair is being held on an area of 1.5 million square feet
and a total of 302 local companies and 86 companies from 27
countries and regions are participating in the fair with an array
of world-class products.
</P>
<P>
The firms and organizations have put on sale their commodities
in 93 pavilions.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time that the fair is put on-line, so people in
other parts of the world can watch it on the computer screen
through the Internet.
</P>
<P>
The export sector of this South Asian country has developed
rapidly since the country's independence in 1971 due to relentless
efforts made by the government.
</P>
<P>
From a paltry earning of 448 million U.S. dollars in 1972-73,
the country achieved an export earning of 5.161 billion dollars in
1997-98, according to the official figures.
</P>
<P>
Besides, Bangladesh is now trying hard to diversify its export
base and expand its international market with a view to earning
more from export. 
</P>
</TEXT>
