<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzania to Re-open Embassy in Kinshasa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, February 2 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania will re-open its
embassy in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) in the next
fiscal year, Deputy Foreign Minister Emmanuel Mwambulukutu has
said.
</P>
<P>
The move is part of Tanzania's strategies to boost economic
co-operation with other African countries, Mwambulukutu was quoted
by media reports Tuesday as saying.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the parliament in the central city of Dodoma Monday,
 Mwambulukutu said Tanzania's embassy in former Zaire was degraded
to a consulate several years ago as a cost cutting measure.
</P>
<P>
For the same reason, the country has lowered it embassy in Rome
to a consulate, and closed its embassies in Angola, Burundi, the
Netherlands and Sudan.
</P>
<P>
The deputy foreign minister, however, said in order to increase
trade and economic co-operation with the neighboring DRC, Tanzania
is prepared to have an embassy in Kinshasa in the next fiscal year
starting July 1999.
</P>
<P>
Mwambuluku further said Tanzania will reinforce its embassies
in all African countries by sending experts as envoys to the
countries.
</P>
<P>
He said a foreign policy is being prepared under which envoys
would be required to concentrate on economic diplomacy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
