<HEADLINE> Disaster Victims to Get Food for Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 2 (Xinhua) -- China's Red Cross Society (CRCS)
plans to send food worth one million yuan ( 120,000 U.S. dollars)
to residents in disaster-hit areas to mark the Spring Festival
celebrations, the country's biggest national holiday.
</P>
<P>
Rice, wheat, flour, meat and other foodstuffs will be
transported to Heilongjiang, Inner Mongolia, Jilin and seven other
provinces and autonomous regions before February 16, when the
Spring Festival falls, according to Gu Yingqi, vice-chairman of
the CRCS.
</P>
<P>
Gu said the activity was an extension of a massive disaster-
relief campaign last year, in which the CRCS raised and allocated
cash and materials worth 808 million yuan to aid regions destroyed
by floods, earthquakes, snow storms and other natural disasters.
</P>
<P>
Five CRCS working teams have been sent to the areas to ensure
the food reaches every needy household, he said.
</P>
<P>
The seven provinces and autonomous regions involved are Anhui,
Jiangxi, Hubei, Hunan, Fujian, Guangxi and Sichuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
