<HEADLINE> Bulls Beaten by Pacers in Final Preseason Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 1 (Xinhua) -- The Indiana Pacers taught
the Chicago Bulls' another lesson Monday night with a 89-83
victory in the final preseason game for both teams in Indianapolis.
</P>
<P>
Even though Toni Kukoc shot 32 points, the game was controlled
by the Pacers most of time.
</P>
<P>
Dale Davis netted 16 points and grabed nine rebounds in 24
minutes, shooting a 50 percent from the free throw line and
blocking three shots.
</P>
<P>
