from a 17-point deficit. The former champion team led three times
briefly.
</P>
<P>
The Pacers, who had beaten the Bulls twice earlier in the
exhibition games, gave their reserves plenty time after taking a
10-point lead, but sent their regular lineup back to the court
with five minutes to go.
</P>
<P>
All five Indiana starters remained on the bench as the Pacers
built a 43-30 halftime lead. 
