<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan Skater Wins Men's 5,000m Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YONGPYONG, South Korea, February 2 (Xinhua) -- Radik
Bikchantayev from Kazakhstan captured his country's second gold
medal at the current Winter Asiad on Tuesday, winning the men's 5,
000 meters speedskating title.
</P>
<P>
Bikchantayev, runner-up behind Japan's Shigekazu Nemoto at the
last Games in Harbin in 1996, won the race by clocking 7 minuts 16.
46 seconds.
</P>
<P>
South Korean Jun Moon took silver in 7:17.97 while Japanese
Kazuki Sawaguchi was third in 7:17.29.
</P>
<P>
Bikchantayev skated in the sixth and last heat with Park Jae-
man of South Korea for the triumph but his time was far below the
world record.
</P>
<P>
It was the second gold medal for Kazakhstan, who won the first
gold Sunday in the men's 15km cross country skiing. 
</P>
