said that the IMF team has split into two groups, one for
examining fiscal policies and macroeconomic indicators, and the
other for reviewing balance of payments, money supply and bank
system supervision.
</P>
<P>
Bier said the assessment is preliminary to talks on Brazil's
economic goals scheduled for the next few days with the
participation of IMF's chief economist Stanley Fisher, who is due
to arrive on Monday. (Brazil-IMF-Crisis Study)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WARSAW -- Poland's currency, the zloty, lost 1.4 percent in
value, falling to 3.736 to the U.S. dollar on Monday, compared to
last Friday.
</P>
<P>
It was the largest devaluation of the Polish currency so far
this year. (Poland-Currency-Devalue) 
