leader Ranil Wickremesinghe threatened to boycott the five
provincial council elections if they are not held on the same day.
</P>
<P>
On January 25, the ruling People's Alliance won the elections
to the North Western Provincial Council despite severe allegations
of violence and violation of election laws.
</P>
<P>
Commissioner of Elections Dayananda Dissanayake will have to
fix the dates for the elections before February 11 in keeping with
the Supreme Court order. 
