<HEADLINE> China's Output of Major Chemical Products Growing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 2 (Xinhua) -- China's chemical industry has
maintained its growth momentum with the output of most major
products keeping on the rise in the first eleven months last year,
according to the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The production of chemical fertilizers between January and
November last year increased 7.2 percent on an annual basis to 27
million tons, and that of chemical pesticides rose 6.4 percent to
551,600 tons.
</P>
<P>
In the 11 months, 4.5 million tons of chemical fiber were
produced, up 10.5 percent, while 4.1 million tons of synthetic
fiber were turned out, up 11.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
The output of ethylene grew 4.9 percent year-on-year to 3.4
million tons and that of plastic products rose 5.8 percent to
seven million tons.
</P>
<P>
The production of caustic soda dropped 2.4 percent to 4.9
million tons, while that of 35-mm cinefilm plunged 57.6 percent to
12.8 million meters.  
</P>
</TEXT>
