<HEADLINE> Chinese Lawmakers Support Constitutional Amendments (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese lawmakers expressed
their support for proposed amendments to the Chinese Constitution
that incorporate Deng Xiaoping Theory as a guiding principle at a
recent legislative session.
</P>
<P>
Feng Xianzhi, a senior legislator and theorist, said at a
discussion about the Constitutional amendments proposed by the
Chinese Communist Party Central Committee that, in contemporary
China, only Deng Xiaoping Theory and no others can address China's
future situation and its destiny, and adding it to the
Constitution will provide a constitutional guarantee for the
reforms and opening up drive,
</P>
<P>
Feng is regarded as a thinker on Marxism, Mao Zedong Thought,
and Deng Xiaoping Theory.
</P>
<P>
Hong Fuzeng and Huang Changxi, who are National People's
Congress Standing Committee members, said that other proposed
changes to the Constitution are in keeping with Deng's theory.
Improving the status of the private sector and adding the
principle of "rule of law" to the Constitution demonstrates the
essence of Deng's theory, Hong emphasized.
</P>
</TEXT>
