<HEADLINE> F.A. to Make Immediate Decision on Hoddle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Glenn Hoddle's future as England
coach will be decided at lunchtime on Tuesday when English
Football Association (F.A) made an announcement about his job
following his controversial remarks about the disabled people.
</P>
<P>
FA executive director David Davies said on Monday:"Clearly we
have had to move quickly to bring people with scheduled
arrangements together but our priority is to do what's right for
English football and the English football team.
</P>
<P>
"Glenn has given his version of events in a couple of TV
interviews and what he said is being considered, although he will
have the chance to say those things first thing tomorrow."
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Hoddle's agent Dennis Roach said the England coach
wanted to issue a libel writ against The Times which carried an
interview last Saturday in which he allegedly said the disabled
people are paying for the sins they committed in an earlier life.
</P>
<P>
Hoddle was quoted as saying: "You and I have been given two
hands and two legs and half-decent brains.
</P>
<P>
"Some people have not been born like that for a reason. The
karma is working from another lifetime."
</P>
<P>
There have been widespread calls for Hoddle's resignation since
the interview was published, but Hoddle said he would not resign
as England coach, a position he has held since the summer of 1996.
</P>
<P>
In television interviews on Monday, Hoddle said: "I never said
it and I don't believe it and I am sorry for the distress I have
caused disabled people and their families."
</P>
<P>
"I made a big, big mistake in taking a journalist into my
confidence, I let my guard down in talking about my personal
beliefs and letting the interview stray from football matters.
</P>
<P>
"I do believe in reincarnation, but to say that I think the
disabled are being punished could not be further from the truth.
</P>
<P>
"I am frustrated that my job is hanging in the balance because
of the way an interview I gave was totally misconstrued and
misunderstood." 
</P>
</TEXT>
