<HEADLINE> Albanian Police Crush Drug-Trafficking Ring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Albanian police uncovered a drug-
trafficking ring on Sunday in Korca district, seizing 85 kilograms
of marijuana from five suspected smugglers.
</P>
<P>
According to the Albanian news agency, police found the
marijuana while making routine checks on Sunday night along the
road from Pogradeci district to Korca.
</P>
<P>
The five suspects, one 25 years old and the other four aged
between 16 and 18, were arrested on the spot. The police also
found in their vehicle two automatic rifles and three loaded
magazines.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, marijuana-planting has become rampant in
southwestern Albania, including Korca.
</P>
<P>
Large amounts of marijuana have been shipped by drug rings from
there to the rest of Albania and abroad.
</P>
<P>
Albanian police have recently uncovered several marijuana-
trafficking groups, but are far from containing drug-trafficking.
</P>
</TEXT>
