<HEADLINE> New Brazilian Lawmakers Sworn In </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, February 1 (Xinhua) -- A total of 86 senators and 513
deputies were sworn in here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The new lawmakers, who will hold their first session on
February 22, are expected to re-elect for another two years
Antonio Carlos Magalhaes as Senate president and Michel Temer as
head of the lower house.
</P>
<P>
