<HEADLINE> Huge fine for Hartson over Attack Incident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Wimbledon striker John Hartson
received a record-equalling 20,000 pounds (US$32,790) fine and
three-match ban on Monday for kicking former West Ham teammate
Eyal Berkovic in the head.
</P>
<P>
Hartson was caught on a supporter's video kicking his Israeli
teammate full in the face during a training session last September.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month Wimbledon set club's new transfer record of
7.5 million pounds ($12.30 million) to buy Hartson from West Ham.
His ban starts on February 15, but is subject to appeal.
</P>
<P>
It was the first time a player had faced a misconduct charge
over a training ground incident but F.A. spokesman Steve Double
said: "We regard the incident as being within our jurisdiction as
John is a professional player, subject to our rules. From the
Football Association's point of view this was regarded as an
unpleasant incident, damaging to the game's image."
</P>
<P>
The fine matches the one handed out to Vinnie Jones for putting
his name to a video of vicious tackles and to Patrick Vieira for
an obscene gesture to the Sheffield Wednesday crowd last September.
</P>
</TEXT>
