<HEADLINE> Brazil, Argentina Prepare Summit Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Argentina and Brazil are
preparing the February 8 summit between presidents Carlos Menem
and Fernando Cardoso, an Argentine official said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Argentina's Industry, Commerce and Mining Minister Alieto
Guadagni was quoted by the press here as saying that the two
presidents will discuss ways for the members of the Mercosur trade
bloc to strengthen their links by modeling on European practice
and eventually adopting a common currency.
</P>
<P>
The member countries must "set clear and defined macroeconomic
goals for the future," and sign a "Maastrich treaty for the
Mercosur," he said.
</P>
<P>
Guadagni added the Mercosur countries are seriously affected by
the devaluation of the Brazilian currency, the real.
</P>
<P>
The meeting between Menem and Cardoso is seen as being crucial
because Argentina and Brazil are two leading members of the trade
bloc and are also mutually dependent, with one third of Argentine
exports going to Brazil.
</P>
<P>
Mercosur, the largest trade bloc in Latin America, groups
Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay, with Chile and Bolivia as
its associate members. 
</P>
</TEXT>
