<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangdong Customs Crackdown on Smuggling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, February 2 (Xinhua) -- The Customs office in
Guangzhou, capital of the booming southern Guangdong Province,
solved 5,688 smuggling cases in 1998, involving goods worth over 4.
09 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Despite a national anti-smuggling campaign which was launched
in the second half of last year, smuggling activities shot up by 5.
1 percent over the previous year, with confiscated goods up 67.8
percent in value.
</P>
<P>
The most conspicuous has been the increase in oil smuggling
along coastal waters carried out by fishing vessels. Guangdong
Customs units seized altogether 240,000 tons of oil in 1998 and
has intercepted another 2,808 tons of oil since the beginning of
this year, according to customs sources.
</P>
<P>
Other hot smuggled items included telecommunication facilities,
computers, integrated circuits and pornographic video CDs, customs
sources said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
