<HEADLINE> Zidane Wins FIFA Player of the Year Award </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, February 1 (Xinhua) -- French World Cup hero Zinedine
Zidane beat his closest challenger Ronaldo to be voted FIFA's
World Player of the Year for 1998 on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Zidane won 93 first-preference votes among the 132 national
coaches who voted and garnered a 518 points against 164 fro
Ronaldo, who won the award in the previous two years.
</P>
<P>
Davor Suker of Croatia, the top scorer in last year's World Cup,
finished third with 108 points.
</P>
<P>
The award for Zidane came as no surprise given the momentous
year the 26-year-old Juventus star had. He won France Football
magazine's prestigious European Player of the Year award just over
two months agao.
</P>
<P>
Zidane accepted the award from Liberian star and 1995 winner
George Weah, speaking briefly only to express his gratitude.
</P>
<P>
Zidane is the first French footballer to take the award since
it was created in 1991. He also tied with Dutch player Dennis
Bergkamp for third place in the contest in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
