<HEADLINE> China Rally to Beat Bulgaria in Dunhill Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, February 2 (Xinhua) -- Defending champions China
overcame a one-goal deficit and 10-man disadvantage to beat
Bulgaria 2-1 in a Group B match of the Dunhill Cup here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Midfielder Sui Dongliang attacked from close range in the 37th
minute to cancel out Bulgaria's 11th minute goal by Antel Stoykov
and close out the first half at 1-1.
</P>
<P>
China, who had their striker Li Yi sent off just two minutes
into the second half for challenging the Bulgarian goalie, showed
the mettle by snatching a winner in the dying minutes of the game
through star striker Zhang Yuning.
</P>
<P>
The victory boosted China's chances of making the next round
after they lost their opening game to South Korea on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In Monday's other matches, South Korea cut a clean 3-0 victory
over Malaysia to book their second round berth on six points.
</P>
<P>
In the final round of group matches on Wednesday, China have to
beat Malaysia to secure their qualification while Bulgaria will
hope to wrench three points from already-qualified South Korea to
keep any hope of advancing to the next round.
</P>
<P>
The 15-game tournament is scheduled to run through February 7.
</P>
</TEXT>
