<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Suzhou Reports Negative Population Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SUZHOU, February 2 (Xinhua) -- This scenic city of east China's
Jiangsu Province reported in 1998 the first negative population
growth since the 1960s.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that a total of 40,487 babies were
born and 42,125 persons died in Suzhou last year, leaving the
natural population growth rate at a negative 0.28 per thousand, a
city official said.
</P>
<P>
The negative growth rate is a result of the family planning
policy in the past decades and that of changed ideas about human
reproduction amid rapid economic and social progress.
</P>
<P>
One of the most popular tourist destinations in China, Suzhou
has an area of 8,488 sq km and a population of 5.75 million, with
the average population density standing at more than 600 persons
per sq km.
</P>
<P>
Suzhou's natural population growth rate was as high as 22.05
per thousand in the 1960s and declined to 18.91 per thousand in
1970, 8.5 per thousand in 1979, and 6.02 per thousand in 1980s.
The downward trend continued steadily in the 1990s.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990202.0330 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-02-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Illegal Tree Fellers Detained in Gansu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, February 2 (Xinhua) -- Public security officers in
northwest China's Gansu Province have detained eight people who
were suspected of felling trees unlawfully and attacked forest
rangers last week.
</P>
<P>
In an attempt to maintain and improve the forest, the
provincial government issued an order last October, banning tree
felling and closed 30 timber companies and outlets. However,
influenced by higher prices for timber, several hundred villagers
in Minxian county clashed with forest rangers, seriously injuring
12 of them. They are still detained in hospital. Three police cars
were also smashed up and a pistol stolen.
</P>
<P>
The incident has greatly concerned the provincial government. A
joint team composed of public security and forest protection
officers has been dispatched to Minxian to make investigations.
</P>
<P>
The government of Minxian county is now calling a public
meeting to explain the importance of protecting the forest to
villagers.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, public security units have increased their patrols
in forest zones. They have already stopped 20 trucks laden with
timber cut down without permission, confiscating 200 cubic meters
of timber.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
