<HEADLINE> Technology Import, Export Booming in Hubei </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, February 2 (Xinhua) -- Hubei Province in central China
reported a total technical import and export value of over 520
million U.S. dollars for 1998, twice 1997's level.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the province's export value recorded 450
million dollars and import value over 60 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
More than 90 percent of the technical export items went to
developed countries, among which Germany, Greece and Sweden
imported 100 million dollars each from Hubei last year.
</P>
<P>
The 30 universities and thousands of scientific research
centers in Hubei can provide for export every year a lot of
scientific and technological developments in shipping, computer
software, numerical control-machine tools and complete plant
equipment.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the province has dozens of major enterprises
for technology import in sectors such as steel, automobiles and
boilers.  
