<HEADLINE> Stocks End Mixed on Wall Street </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Stocks ended mixed on Wall
Street Monday as investors responded to different news from
economic and financial sections.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed at 9,345.70, down
13.13. The index opened stronger but retreated later, and it
rallied again in a second time early afternoon but plunged before
the close of trading.
</P>
<P>
The technology heavy Nasdaq composite was up 4.20 at 2,510.09
in the close of trading but Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was lower
6.61 at 1,273.03.
</P>
<P>
The market buoyed early morning on a report from the Commerce
Department that Americans' personal income surged 0.5 percent in
December, the best gain in 10 months, and that personal spending
rose 0.8 percent, the biggest in seven months.
</P>
<P>
Stock prices were also supported by a report that Rohm &AMP; Haas
agreed to buy salt processor Morton International in a transaction
worth 4.9 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
But investors were cautious ahead of a Federal Reserve policy
meeting that begins Tuesday. Earlier, some Federal Reserve
officials have tried to cool the market advances down.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index was down 2.98 at 597.46 and the American Stock
Exchange Index was down 2.23 at 712.63. 
</P>
</TEXT>
