<HEADLINE> European Stock Markets Post Strong Gains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, February 1 (Xinhua) -- European stock markets posted
strong gains Monday after news of mergers in the banking and
insurance markets.
</P>
<P>
London's FTSE 100 of leading shares hit a peak of 6045 in mid
afternoon when it stood up 149 points, but it later calmed to
close up 116.4 points to 6012.4.
</P>
<P>
Guardian Royal Exchange said it had agreed to a 3.4 billion
pound (5.44 billion U.S. dollars) takeover by Sun Life and
Provincial Holdings Plc, majority controlled by France's Axa.
</P>
<P>
The banking sector also had a boost following tie-ups between
French banks Paribas and Societe Generale.
</P>
<P>
Observers here said the move prompted expectation of further
consolidation in the banking business, or at least the hope that
competition would prompt greater cost efficiencies.
</P>
<P>
German shares also moved ahead on gains in financials following
the merger of the two major French banks. The leading Dax index
closed up 31 points at 5190.
</P>
<P>
French stocks were led higher by shares in the financial sector
after the announcement of major mergers and acquisitions before
the market opened. The leading Cac 40 index finished 52 points
ahead at 4304.
</P>
<P>
The creation of SG Paribas marks a long-awaited concentration
in the French banking sector. And it is also believed the merger
promises more to come.  
</P>
</TEXT>
