<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 21:15 GMT, February 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Iraqi President Saddam Hussein has offered huge
awards for anyone who shoots down any U.S. or British jet
violating Iraq's airspace, a newspaper here reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Nabdh al-Shabab weekly said Saddam has ordered to post
the bounty of 25 million Iraqi dinars (about 13,500 dollars) for
any Iraqi who brings down an allied warplane.
</P>
<P>
The weekly said anyone who shoots down a U.S. or British
missile will be awarded 10 million dinars (about 5,400 dollars),
and 5 million dinars (about 2,700 dollars) will be given to those
who capture a U.S. or British pilot. (BC-Iraq-US-Award)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- A tourist bus overturned when it ran into a truck and
was hit by another one in northern Egypt Monday, injuring 31
German tourists and three Egyptians.
</P>
<P>
The accident took place in Wadi al Natroun at the center of the
190-kilometer desert road linking Cairo and Mediterranean port
city of Alexandria, a source of Egypt's Information Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Heavy fog was the primary cause behind the accident, but full
investigation is still underway, the source said.
(BC-Egypt-Accident)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NICOSIA -- Two Israelis were sentenced to three and a half
years in prison in Cyprus Monday for approaching a prohibited
military area and possessing banned listening equipment without
due permission.
</P>
<P>
Igal Damary, 49, and Udi Hargov, 37, were arrested in early
November last year at the small fishing village of Zigi on the
Cypriot southern coast and found carrying radio scanners, a
lap-top computer, cell phones and eight maps of the island.
(BC-Cyprus-Israelis)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran started on Monday celebrations of the 20th
anniversary of the Islamic revolution amid intensified power
struggles and concerns over the country's economy.
</P>
<P>
School bells rang and helicopters showered flowers on the
shrine of Ayatollah Ruhollah Musavi Khomeini, founder of the
Islamic Republic, to mark his return from a 15-year exile the same
day 20 years ago.
</P>
<P>
A large crowd gathered inside the shrine to pay tribute to
Khomeini, who masterminded the Islamic revolution which toppled
the former pro-U.S. Pahlavi regime in 1979.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to the crowd, former Iranian President Hashemi
Rafsanjani called for unity among the people despite their
differences. (BC-Iran-Revolution-Celebration)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Members of the Islamic militant group Hamas shot
to death a Palestinian policeman on Monday in south Gaza Strip,
Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The report said the policeman of the security forces of the
Palestinian National Authority (PNA) was trying to arrest the two
Hamas members when they opened fire at him.
</P>
<P>
The identity of the two Hamas members were not officially
confirmed. But the report said they were Hamas fugitives.
(BC-Palestine-Hamas) 
</P>
</TEXT>
